Your job is simple, if x squared is more than 1000, return It's hotter than the sun!!, else, return Help yourself to a honeycomb Yorkie for the glovebox.

Note: Input will either be a positive integer (or a string for untyped languages).




function apple(x){ 
//if input squared is > 1000 return It's hotter than the sun!! else return Help yourself to a honeycomb Yorkie for the glovebox.
//input can be a string or positive integer
//Normalize the input and write the condition 
  if (Number(x)**2 > 1000){
    return "It's hotter than the sun!!"
  } else {
    return "Help yourself to a honeycomb Yorkie for the glovebox."
  }
}
